## Applying This Rule

When writing new decompression code:
1. Route first, execute second — never try/catch/fallback
2. If a path can fail for valid input, fix the path, don't add fallback
3. If a path is not ready, don't wire it into production
4. Tests must assert exact correctness, never "approximate or fallback"
5. Run `cargo test --release correctness_tests` after any decompression change
